cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about medical image segmentation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed module involves combining multiple kernel sizes, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed module, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
